WEBVTT

00:04.091 --> 00:06.397
President Nixon asked for me.

00:06.528 --> 00:08.965
We got a kinda
special opportunity for you.

00:09.096 --> 00:11.576
Now, there's a CIA reject
named Howard Hunt

00:11.707 --> 00:15.102
currently graduating
from rooting out leaks

00:15.232 --> 00:16.799
to, uh,
rat-fuckin' the Democrats.

00:16.929 --> 00:20.411
We must become snakes.

00:21.543 --> 00:22.587
I don't think I can make it
to see you this weekend.

00:22.718 --> 00:24.372
I'll talk to you soon.

00:24.459 --> 00:27.940
Winnie, I decided long ago
that I will say how I feel,

00:28.071 --> 00:29.290
and if that does not conform

00:29.420 --> 00:31.422
to the president's message,
so be it.

00:31.509 --> 00:33.033
You reading poetry now?

00:33.163 --> 00:34.556
I'm in a bit
of a wistful mood, I guess,

00:34.686 --> 00:36.993
thinking about a-a boy
I once knew.

00:37.124 --> 00:39.517
And once in a while,
you still wonder

00:39.604 --> 00:40.779
what it might have been like

00:40.910 --> 00:43.695
if you had stayed
in Pine Bluff.

00:43.826 --> 00:46.002
Mr. McCord, my family and I,
we are traveling out

00:46.089 --> 00:48.091
to California for a fundraiser.

00:48.222 --> 00:49.919
I was wondering if you would
like to accompany us there.

00:50.050 --> 00:51.834
I would love to, Mrs. Mitchell,

00:51.964 --> 00:54.793
but the campaign
does have me very busy.

00:54.924 --> 00:58.275
It seems there was a mix-up
at the Watergate!

00:58.406 --> 00:59.624
-The lobby.
-Get out now.

00:59.711 --> 01:02.105
A-a door
was taped incorrectly.

01:02.236 --> 01:04.412
McCord did not get away.

01:04.542 --> 01:06.109
You really think
that when Martha sees his face

01:06.240 --> 01:07.806
in the newspaper,
she won't call

01:07.937 --> 01:08.981
one of her journalist friends?

01:09.112 --> 01:10.374
Where is everyone?

01:10.505 --> 01:11.897
Mr. Mitchell had to fly
to Washington.

01:11.984 --> 01:13.551
His instructions
were to have you wait here.

01:13.638 --> 01:14.987
This is ridiculous.
I am calling my husband.

01:17.816 --> 01:19.122
You are not in charge here.

01:19.253 --> 01:20.776
-Do you understand me?
-Mm-hmm.

01:27.826 --> 01:30.264
Martha, what'd they
do to you, sweetheart?

01:32.440 --> 01:34.006
If you don't tell me
what them girls did,

01:34.094 --> 01:35.182
I can't do a thing
to help you.

01:36.661 --> 01:38.098
They told me I was trash.

01:40.012 --> 01:42.363
Mm-hmm. Why'd they say that?

01:46.062 --> 01:47.107
Junebug.

01:50.066 --> 01:51.633
They said my daddy runs around.

01:53.939 --> 01:55.724
You believe 'em?

01:59.162 --> 02:00.859
Hmm.

02:00.990 --> 02:04.254
Then you tried to run off,
and...

02:04.385 --> 02:05.342
they chase you down.

02:06.996 --> 02:08.128
Beat you up.

02:10.652 --> 02:11.957
They spat on me.

02:16.484 --> 02:17.876
My poor little girl.

02:23.012 --> 02:24.187
Hey, I want to show you
something.

02:26.929 --> 02:29.671
When your
great-great-grandfather

02:29.801 --> 02:31.281
left England
for South Carolina,

02:31.368 --> 02:34.371
he was given this timepiece

02:34.502 --> 02:37.635
as a traveling gift
from his cousin.

02:40.160 --> 02:41.465
Now, you know
who his cousin was?

02:45.382 --> 02:48.429
King George III of England.

02:51.040 --> 02:53.303
From your
great-great-grandfather

02:53.434 --> 02:54.957
to your grandfather

02:55.087 --> 02:57.612
to you and me,

02:57.699 --> 03:00.615
the Bealls are descended
from nobility.

03:02.617 --> 03:03.792
Hmm?

03:03.922 --> 03:06.534
That makes you a princess,

03:06.664 --> 03:09.014
your mother a queen,

03:09.145 --> 03:11.930
and me?

03:12.061 --> 03:13.193
A king.

03:15.934 --> 03:17.849
So next time
somebody tries to treat you

03:17.980 --> 03:19.808
like you're nothing,

03:19.938 --> 03:21.331
you fight back.

03:23.115 --> 03:26.031
'Cause your blood,
it's worth fighting for.

03:27.990 --> 03:30.384
Yes, sir.

03:30.514 --> 03:32.734
Oh, and one more thing.

03:32.864 --> 03:36.085
Any of them girls ever tries
to touch you again,

03:36.216 --> 03:38.261
take one of their fingers.

03:38.348 --> 03:42.309
Pull it back... 'til it pops.

03:44.180 --> 03:47.705
They'll likely
pee themselves...

03:47.836 --> 03:49.403
or run away.

04:35.449 --> 04:36.276
Hello?

04:37.886 --> 04:40.497
She's doing just fine.

04:40.584 --> 04:43.848
I'm keeping her away
from phones and newspapers.

04:43.979 --> 04:47.069
No, Steve's out sick,
but Barry's here with me.

04:47.199 --> 04:48.897
Of course.
Oh, she's very comfortable.

04:49.027 --> 04:49.811
Thank you.

05:11.789 --> 05:12.399
Excuse me.

05:14.183 --> 05:17.404
-Miss? Excuse me.

05:17.491 --> 05:19.362
Mrs. Mitchell, is everything
all right in there?

05:19.493 --> 05:20.668
Excuse me.

05:20.798 --> 05:22.539
-Ma'am?

05:25.803 --> 05:27.457
Mrs. Mitchell, unlock the door.

05:27.588 --> 05:29.590
My God. Excuse me!

05:29.720 --> 05:30.678
-Mrs. Mitchell...
-Hola!

05:30.808 --> 05:32.070
...if you don't unlock
this door,

05:32.201 --> 05:33.115
I'll have no choice
but to break it down.

05:33.202 --> 05:34.725
Miss, I need h--

05:38.425 --> 05:39.991
No, no, no!

05:40.122 --> 05:41.253
-Ma'am?

05:46.433 --> 05:48.609
What in heaven's name
are you doing?

05:48.739 --> 05:50.959
-Why didn't you answer me?

05:51.089 --> 05:53.875
Because I'm not
a trained parakeet.

05:53.962 --> 05:55.790
But if you're gonna
keep me caged up like one,

05:55.920 --> 05:57.182
the least you could do
is get me something to eat.

06:02.144 --> 06:03.363
I'll send someone out.

06:41.923 --> 06:43.533
Don't let him push you around.

06:43.664 --> 06:45.840
You got this.

06:45.970 --> 06:48.451
-You're an animal.

06:48.582 --> 06:51.541
You're a fuckin' animal.
It's fuck or get fucked.

06:51.672 --> 06:53.543
Hey, Dean, where's
that coffee at, sweetheart?

06:53.674 --> 06:55.545
Yup, yup.
One pot of hot joe coming up.

06:58.330 --> 06:59.506
All right.

07:05.816 --> 07:07.122
Took you long enough.

07:07.252 --> 07:08.428
You know you're supposed
to brew the coffee,

07:08.558 --> 07:09.777
not fuck it, right?

07:11.692 --> 07:14.956
Goddamn cocksucking thing.

07:15.086 --> 07:16.174
Something the matter, sir?

07:16.305 --> 07:17.741
Yeah, it's these
goddamn pipe stems.

07:17.872 --> 07:19.961
I never know
which one goes with which.

07:20.091 --> 07:22.224
Martha's got a whole system,
and--

07:22.354 --> 07:24.095
God damn it.

07:24.226 --> 07:26.620
How's she doing
in California, sir?

07:26.750 --> 07:27.534
I'm sure she's having

07:27.664 --> 07:29.405
a little party down there.

07:29.536 --> 07:32.321
So here's where we're at.

07:32.452 --> 07:36.847
We got five little Indians
under arrest at Metro booking.

07:36.978 --> 07:38.632
That includes
McCord and the Cubans, right?

07:38.762 --> 07:40.329
Bingo was his name-o.

07:40.460 --> 07:42.505
Now, miraculously,
Liddy and Hunt

07:42.636 --> 07:44.072
managed to avoid capture

07:44.202 --> 07:45.334
without falling
into an open sewer,

07:45.465 --> 07:47.728
so we're aces on that front.

07:47.858 --> 07:51.558
And they covered their tracks,
mostly.

07:51.688 --> 07:53.516
Mostly?

07:53.647 --> 07:57.302
Well, there is still the small,
uh, issue of Hunt's safe.

07:57.389 --> 08:00.871
-Wh--you had a safe?
-Yeah.

08:01.002 --> 08:03.134
Yeah, in my office at the
White House, I had a safe.

08:03.265 --> 08:05.702
You were, uh, conducting, uh,

08:05.789 --> 08:07.312
criminal operations
on behalf of the president

08:07.399 --> 08:09.401
and somebody gave you an office
at the White House?

08:09.532 --> 08:11.621
Yeah. Wasn't a big office.

08:11.752 --> 08:13.405
Well, what's in it, the safe?

08:13.536 --> 08:14.276
Well, let's just say
there's some--

08:14.406 --> 08:17.061
you know, some highly...

08:17.192 --> 08:19.411
secretive documents
I r-really wouldn't want,

08:19.542 --> 08:22.458
uh, the light of day to see,
know what I mean?

08:22.589 --> 08:23.938
What do you mean by that?
Can you elaborate?

08:24.068 --> 08:25.330
All right, all right,
so you just need

08:25.461 --> 08:27.071
to give us the combination.

08:27.202 --> 08:27.985
-Then we can get somebody...
-Can't. Can't.

08:28.116 --> 08:29.378
...to go over there,
empty it out.

08:29.509 --> 08:30.684
Can't.
Don't know the combination.

08:30.814 --> 08:32.120
How do you not know
the combination?

08:32.207 --> 08:34.122
Because I forgot it.

08:34.252 --> 08:35.732
-Oh, you forgot it?
-Yes, I forgot it.

08:35.863 --> 08:37.125
I don't have a good memory
when it comes to combinations

08:37.255 --> 08:38.953
or, you know, those things.

08:39.083 --> 08:40.084
Fuck! I mean what the fuck?

08:40.215 --> 08:41.259
Calm down.

08:41.390 --> 08:42.739
We'll just handle it
another way.

08:42.870 --> 08:44.480
It's, like,
two-two-five-six-six or--

08:44.611 --> 08:46.221
Two-two-five.

08:46.351 --> 08:48.179
No. That's not it.
That's my daughter's birthday.

08:48.310 --> 08:49.006
You don't want that.

08:50.965 --> 08:52.096
Okay. Can't we just--can't we
just blow it up?

08:52.227 --> 08:53.620
How hard is it
to blow up a safe?

08:53.750 --> 08:55.535
Uh, if I may interject
as a-a small point, sir,

08:55.622 --> 08:56.492
this is all beginning
to sound a lot

08:56.579 --> 08:58.233
like destruction of evidence.

08:58.320 --> 08:59.451
One-six-one-zero-eight-three.

08:59.539 --> 09:01.279
You're making it sound
so serious.

09:01.410 --> 09:03.499
No, no.
That's the golden ratio.

09:03.630 --> 09:05.022
-Uh, d--
-The golden ratio?

09:05.153 --> 09:06.807
Don't we have guys who can--
who can take care

09:06.937 --> 09:08.983
of this kind of stuff,
you know--

09:09.113 --> 09:11.942
-What? Crime guys?
-You're looking at 'em.

09:12.029 --> 09:15.163
Oh, I know.
It's seven-six-six-four-four.

09:15.293 --> 09:16.817
Seven-seven-six-four-four.

09:16.947 --> 09:19.167
No, no. That's D-Day.
That's not it.

09:19.297 --> 09:21.212
I don't know what the--
I don't know.

09:21.343 --> 09:22.823
All right, this is bullshit.
Hunt should just do it.

09:22.953 --> 09:24.128
It's his safe, for Pete's sake.

09:24.259 --> 09:25.216
No. Fuck no.

09:25.347 --> 09:26.435
I don't want that dipshit

09:26.566 --> 09:27.958
or his psychotic friend

09:28.089 --> 09:30.221
anywhere near
the White House ever again.

09:30.308 --> 09:31.745
No offense, son.

09:31.875 --> 09:33.660
No. God no. None taken, sir.

09:33.790 --> 09:35.575
Well, we've gotta stop
farting around here,

09:35.705 --> 09:37.402
fellas, and get real.

09:37.489 --> 09:39.666
Unless we want to be
on the business end

09:39.796 --> 09:41.537
of an investigative committee
before Christmas,

09:41.668 --> 09:43.583
one of us has to get
that goddamn safe

09:43.713 --> 09:44.714
out of the White House.

10:00.034 --> 10:02.253
Oh, no, no, no.
No, I couldn't do it.

10:02.384 --> 10:04.604
I-I'm-I'm too close
to the president.

10:29.977 --> 10:31.543
Here's the file,
Agent Lano.

10:38.246 --> 10:39.377
Special Agent Lano.

10:39.508 --> 10:40.291
Yeah?

10:42.772 --> 10:45.166
Ah, gracias, amigo.

10:45.253 --> 10:46.341
Appreciate it, bud.

10:51.433 --> 10:53.261
He's a big guy, isn't he?

10:53.348 --> 10:54.349
What?

10:54.436 --> 10:55.742
He's a big guy.

10:55.872 --> 10:57.657
Yeah. He's, uh, very solid.

10:59.963 --> 11:02.618
-So you want to go in or--
-Yeah, I plan to.

11:02.749 --> 11:05.403
Just, uh, waiting on the agent
on assignment.

11:05.490 --> 11:06.578
He's running a little late.

11:13.585 --> 11:14.717
You're the agent?

11:14.848 --> 11:17.502
-That's right.
-Oh, fuck. Fuck.

11:17.633 --> 11:20.288
I'm sorry.
Uh, this isn't because you're--

11:20.418 --> 11:22.377
No, of-of course not.
Please keep it.

11:22.507 --> 11:24.553
-You sure?
-I insist.

11:24.684 --> 11:26.947
I'm sorry, yeah, ma--
uh, it makes sense

11:27.077 --> 11:31.038
because we're dealing
with a Cuban burglar,

11:31.168 --> 11:32.735
so they would send a,
you know--

11:37.044 --> 11:39.437
-Mm-hmm.
-What's your name again?

11:39.524 --> 11:41.744
Agent Paul Magallanes, sir,
reporting for duty.

11:42.397 --> 11:44.573
-"Maggy-anus"?
-Magallanes.

11:44.704 --> 11:46.706
"Maga-yah-nez, yah-nez."

11:46.793 --> 11:48.708
-Magallanes.
-Say it slow.

11:48.838 --> 11:50.361
You can just call me Paul.

11:50.492 --> 11:51.885
-Paul.
-Yes.

11:52.015 --> 11:54.539
Angelo Lano.
Pleasure to meet you.

11:54.670 --> 11:55.845
I didn't know they sent feds

11:55.976 --> 11:58.282
to investigate
routine burglaries.

11:58.413 --> 11:59.501
I'm afraid
it's standard procedure

11:59.631 --> 12:01.503
when foreign nationals
are involved.

12:01.633 --> 12:03.026
Cigarette, Mr. McCord?

12:03.157 --> 12:04.027
No, thanks.

12:04.158 --> 12:05.855
Now, Mr. McCord,

12:05.942 --> 12:08.205
you said in your statement
that you personally hired

12:08.336 --> 12:12.079
the Cubans--Gonzalez, Martinez,
Sturgis, Barker--

12:12.209 --> 12:15.299
to help you rob DNC
headquarters at the Watergate.

12:16.300 --> 12:18.085
It says here that you were
the only contact

12:18.215 --> 12:19.826
for these guys in D.C.

12:19.956 --> 12:22.393
Is-is that--is that correct?

12:22.524 --> 12:24.265
If that's what I said.

12:24.395 --> 12:26.658
It's funny, because...

12:26.789 --> 12:30.053
Barker gave us
this address book,

12:30.140 --> 12:32.664
and a name--
got a lot of names in here,

12:32.795 --> 12:34.579
but one of 'em that stood out,
right here.

12:36.538 --> 12:37.800
HH.

12:37.931 --> 12:39.628
That's a D.C. number.

12:39.759 --> 12:41.282
Recently disconnected.

12:41.369 --> 12:42.718
Ring a bell?

12:42.849 --> 12:44.502
It's like I said.

12:44.633 --> 12:46.548
The whole thing
was my planning,

12:46.678 --> 12:49.159
my execution, my guys.

12:49.290 --> 12:51.901
If you want any more, I'm gonna
need my lawyer present.

12:52.032 --> 12:52.728
All right.

12:54.643 --> 12:55.949
Here's the thing, Mr. McCord.

12:57.515 --> 12:58.995
I think you're full of shit.

12:59.126 --> 13:01.258
I don't think this was
a simple break-in.

13:01.389 --> 13:02.782
I don't think you're nearly
the B&E mastermind

13:02.912 --> 13:04.044
that you claim to be,

13:04.174 --> 13:06.873
especially after hearing
from the Cubans.

13:07.003 --> 13:08.875
The Cubans?

13:08.962 --> 13:10.224
They kept asking
what kind of idiota

13:10.354 --> 13:12.748
tapes a door latch side to side

13:12.879 --> 13:14.228
when everybody knows
you do it vertical

13:14.358 --> 13:16.012
so nobody can see
the tape sticking out.

13:16.143 --> 13:17.144
Well, that's bullshit.

13:19.233 --> 13:22.149
The tape can slip
if it's vertical.

13:26.022 --> 13:27.458
All right.

13:27.545 --> 13:29.199
Listen, amigo,
vertical, sideways,

13:29.330 --> 13:30.940
it doesn't matter to me.

13:31.071 --> 13:32.376
I'm not here to debate
the tape thing with you,

13:32.507 --> 13:34.161
all right?

13:34.291 --> 13:36.598
I am gonna tell you,
you say you were in charge.

13:36.728 --> 13:37.860
The Cubans don't sound like

13:37.947 --> 13:39.470
they respect
their superior too much.

13:39.557 --> 13:42.212
They don't respect me. Ha!

13:42.343 --> 13:45.346
That's a laugh.
Lie down with dogs, I guess.

13:45.433 --> 13:46.913
Lie down with dogs.

13:48.653 --> 13:51.004
You're saying the Cubans...
are dogs.

13:53.223 --> 13:55.356
I'm not sure.
You tell me, amigo.

13:57.227 --> 13:58.881
That racist piece of shit.

13:59.012 --> 14:01.057
He wouldn't hire those Cubans
to paint his goddamn house.

14:01.188 --> 14:02.885
I don't see him being
in charge of this, do you?

14:02.972 --> 14:03.886
Whatever it is, these guys

14:03.973 --> 14:05.714
are five steps ahead of us.

14:05.845 --> 14:07.150
Maybe they're CIA.

14:07.281 --> 14:08.848
Maybe it's like those bombings
in New York,

14:08.978 --> 14:10.240
like, an anti-Castro thing.

14:10.371 --> 14:13.026
Big bankroll. Dry runs.
Lookouts.

14:14.549 --> 14:16.725
-Lookouts?
-Worth a shot.

14:22.513 --> 14:23.775
Lunch is served.

14:40.618 --> 14:42.490
Your foie gras, madam.

14:54.328 --> 14:55.851
Thought you were hungry.

14:55.982 --> 14:57.635
Seems to have faded.

15:02.075 --> 15:03.119
Nice watch.

15:05.382 --> 15:06.644
It's a family heirloom.

15:06.775 --> 15:08.255
Was a gift
from the king of England.

15:08.385 --> 15:10.083
No kidding.

15:10.213 --> 15:12.476
My father gave it to me.

15:12.607 --> 15:14.652
Passed away when I was young.

15:14.783 --> 15:15.740
Sorry to hear that.

15:20.702 --> 15:22.486
Why you doing this?

15:22.617 --> 15:24.836
-Doing what?
-Keeping me here,

15:24.924 --> 15:27.187
participating in this
callous enterprise.

15:27.317 --> 15:30.016
You don't seem like a sadist
or a psychopath.

15:30.146 --> 15:31.495
That's sweet of you to say.

15:33.062 --> 15:34.281
What would your wife say

15:34.411 --> 15:35.456
if she knew you were
holding me prisoner?

15:37.066 --> 15:38.850
Probably tell me
to be home by dinner.

15:40.548 --> 15:41.810
Well, that's very sad.

15:47.598 --> 15:49.339
I sleep fine at night, lady,

15:49.470 --> 15:50.732
because I know my place

15:50.862 --> 15:52.429
in this whole
messy enterprise of ours.

15:52.560 --> 15:54.692
People like you?

15:54.823 --> 15:57.869
Oh, you have the luxury of
pretending you're above it all.

15:58.000 --> 16:02.091
It's other people who have to
sacrifice for Nixon's vision,

16:02.222 --> 16:03.484
but when it's your turn
to pitch in,

16:03.614 --> 16:05.529
when the gun's turned on you,

16:05.660 --> 16:07.140
it's suddenly a tragedy.

16:09.620 --> 16:12.493
You're very cruel, aren't you?

16:12.623 --> 16:13.668
And you're a hypocrite.

16:17.628 --> 16:18.803
Spare a cigarette?

16:21.893 --> 16:22.982
They're not menthol.

16:24.853 --> 16:26.376
Beggars can't be choosers.

16:37.431 --> 16:38.475
Thank you.

16:40.086 --> 16:40.825
You're welcome.

16:46.918 --> 16:48.181
Barry!

16:48.311 --> 16:49.921
Barry, get a doctor
up here now!

16:51.575 --> 16:53.621
It's only a second-degree burn,

16:53.751 --> 16:55.797
so it should heal up soon.

16:55.927 --> 16:58.060
You're lucky that, uh,

16:58.191 --> 16:59.888
your friend was here
to help you.

17:00.019 --> 17:02.282
No, please.
You need to help me.

17:02.412 --> 17:04.980
The-the situation
is not as it appears.

17:05.111 --> 17:07.678
I know all about
your situation.

17:07.765 --> 17:09.550
It's nothing to be
embarrassed about.

17:09.637 --> 17:13.075
A lot of women your age
suffer from paranoid episodes.

17:13.162 --> 17:15.121
No, no, no.
You don't understand.

17:17.166 --> 17:18.907
I'm being held against my will.

17:19.038 --> 17:21.562
They've cut the cord
on my phone.

17:21.692 --> 17:23.912
Maybe a little time away
from your telephone

17:24.043 --> 17:25.870
