Mrs. Mitchell.

17:26.001 --> 17:29.396
Maybe that's just
what you need right now.

17:35.924 --> 17:37.708
Yes.

17:37.839 --> 17:39.406
That's right. Thank you.

17:44.628 --> 17:48.719
Could you, uh, get me a glass
of water before you go?

17:48.806 --> 17:50.895
-Oh, absolutely.
-Thank you.

17:54.203 --> 17:55.117
How is she?

17:55.204 --> 17:56.814
Her delusions will pass.

17:56.945 --> 17:59.382
Until then, be sure
to keep an eye on her.

17:59.469 --> 18:00.731
Don't worry.
I'll take good care of her.

18:07.564 --> 18:08.652
I can't believe they trusted
Hunt with an office,

18:08.739 --> 18:09.871
let alone a safe.

18:10.001 --> 18:11.786
Fucking Mitchell.

18:12.613 --> 18:15.268
-I know why he's doing this.
-Hmm.

18:15.355 --> 18:16.095
He's jealous
the president likes me.

18:17.618 --> 18:19.707
Wants to keep Nixon
all for himself.

18:19.837 --> 18:21.665
You're talking about him
like he's David Cassidy.

18:21.752 --> 18:22.884
-John Dean's office.

18:23.014 --> 18:24.799
Check the handle.
The GSA cracked it.

18:24.886 --> 18:27.454
-They cracked it?

18:27.584 --> 18:29.195
Mr. Dean, I have
your mechanic on the line.

18:29.325 --> 18:30.413
Oh, great.

18:31.632 --> 18:33.503
This is John Dean.

18:33.590 --> 18:35.114
Uh-huh.

18:35.244 --> 18:36.506
The transmission? Really?

18:36.637 --> 18:38.421
Well, uh,
when can I get her in?

18:38.552 --> 18:40.206
What? Next month?

18:40.293 --> 18:44.210
Well, can't I pay
a-a rush fee or something?

18:44.340 --> 18:46.342
Ugh. Fine.

18:48.083 --> 18:49.302
Oh, God damn it.

18:51.217 --> 18:52.870
Fucking Porsche.

18:53.001 --> 18:54.872
I finally talked Mo
into coming back to D.C.,

18:55.003 --> 18:57.136
and she's just been sitting
around my house waiting for me.

18:57.266 --> 18:59.573
Well, I hate to make things
worse for you here, boss,

18:59.703 --> 19:01.140
but I think possession
of this safe alone

19:01.270 --> 19:02.532
is grounds for treason.

19:02.663 --> 19:05.187
I mean, this appears
to be a CIA cable

19:05.318 --> 19:07.058
directly implicating Kennedy
in the Bay of Pigs.

19:07.189 --> 19:09.017
What? Give me that.

19:09.148 --> 19:11.585
-Mr. Dean's office.

19:11.672 --> 19:14.805
Here's a proposal to firebomb
the Brookings Institution.

19:14.936 --> 19:16.590
-What?
-Zany.

19:16.720 --> 19:18.200
Oh!

19:18.287 --> 19:19.375
Not to mention
this little number.

19:19.462 --> 19:20.898
Boom!

19:20.985 --> 19:21.769
Jesus. Put that away.

19:25.599 --> 19:28.036
What the hell?

19:28.167 --> 19:31.300
So Hunt just had this stuff
lying around the office?

19:31.387 --> 19:32.780
But why?

19:32.867 --> 19:33.955
Because he's
the personification

19:34.085 --> 19:35.435
of the rotten core

19:35.565 --> 19:36.914
at the center
of the national myth?

19:37.045 --> 19:37.872
If I get caught
with this stuff,

19:38.002 --> 19:38.873
I could go to prison for years.

19:39.003 --> 19:40.179
Oh, decades, probably.

19:42.572 --> 19:44.487
I swear to God,
John Mitchell's out to get me.

19:44.574 --> 19:46.141
Whoa.
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

19:46.228 --> 19:48.970
You're looking at this
all wrong, okay?

19:49.100 --> 19:50.972
This is how you get in
with the president,

19:51.102 --> 19:53.279
okay, because if you take care
of this for him,

19:53.409 --> 19:56.064
he'll know he can trust you,
and he'll owe you one.

19:56.195 --> 19:58.284
So here's what you're gonna do.

19:58.371 --> 19:59.720
You're gonna have a nice night
out with your lady friend,

19:59.850 --> 20:01.939
and then you're gonna find
a big, empty field.

20:02.070 --> 20:03.245
You're gonna burn
all of this shit,

20:03.332 --> 20:04.681
and you're gonna
throw this gun in a lake.

20:04.768 --> 20:07.771
Yeah. Okay.

20:07.902 --> 20:09.773
Okay. Send my best to Mo.

20:31.795 --> 20:33.536
Aw, fuck.

20:35.669 --> 20:37.192
God.

20:48.682 --> 20:49.987
Fuck.

21:04.350 --> 21:05.699
Oh, God. Fuck!

21:07.875 --> 21:08.789
Fuck!

21:11.182 --> 21:12.401
Fuck.

21:12.532 --> 21:13.446
Okay.

21:15.970 --> 21:16.971
Ugh!

21:19.626 --> 21:21.628
-Ugh!

21:21.758 --> 21:23.325
Oh, fuck!

21:34.293 --> 21:36.730
Fuck. Fuck.

21:38.427 --> 21:39.646
-Hey, son.

21:42.170 --> 21:43.998
Son, what the heck
you doing on my property?

21:46.130 --> 21:47.697
You trying to start
a fire out here?

21:47.828 --> 21:49.873
No, no. No.

21:50.004 --> 21:52.746
No, I had car trouble,
and, uh...

21:52.876 --> 21:54.748
and I got lost
and then came out here.

21:54.878 --> 21:56.097
You know,
thought I'd have a-a cigarette,

21:56.227 --> 21:58.229
and-and, uh,

21:58.360 --> 22:00.710
I had...

22:00.841 --> 22:02.059
gasoline.

22:07.935 --> 22:09.806
Oh, fuck.

22:09.937 --> 22:10.720
What the--

22:22.645 --> 22:24.212
Oh, fuck.

23:43.422 --> 23:45.162
Okay. You love Christmas.

23:50.341 --> 23:52.256
-Oh, boy.

24:07.228 --> 24:09.143
Hmm.

24:19.588 --> 24:21.198
Well, this is it.

24:21.329 --> 24:24.375
Okay, son. You take it easy.

24:24.506 --> 24:27.074
Thank you, sir.
I really do appreciate this.

24:27.161 --> 24:29.032
You're very welcome.
See you in the morning.

24:35.125 --> 24:36.605
Where were you?
Who was that?

24:36.692 --> 24:38.477
Hey.

24:38.607 --> 24:41.262
I had a little car trouble,

24:41.392 --> 24:44.091
and this kind gentleman
helped me out.

24:44.178 --> 24:46.006
I'm...

24:46.093 --> 24:48.661
I'm gonna have that fucking
Porsche towed back here.

24:48.791 --> 24:50.053
I'm gonna sell it for scrap.

24:52.795 --> 24:54.144
Let's get you in the shower.

24:54.275 --> 24:55.929
You smell like gasoline.

24:56.059 --> 24:57.278
Did you get
some writing done?

24:57.365 --> 24:59.149
Oh, I almost did,
and then I found

24:59.236 --> 25:00.934
this "Fuck Communism" sign.

25:01.064 --> 25:02.370
Oh, yeah,
that's pretty neat, isn't it?

25:02.501 --> 25:03.980
You like that? I had that
specially commissioned.

25:04.111 --> 25:05.068
I do like it.

27:27.341 --> 27:28.516
All right, well,
then what would you call it?

27:28.647 --> 27:31.214
-Well, it's Nixon shock.

27:31.345 --> 27:33.652
So, Winnie, what's it like
on the Martha Mitchell beat?

27:33.782 --> 27:36.132
Oh, she's really not that bad

27:36.263 --> 27:37.612
once you get to know her,
honestly.

27:37.743 --> 27:39.745
She's a retrograde
segregationist.

27:39.875 --> 27:41.442
If you ask me,
she has blood on her hands.

27:41.572 --> 27:43.226
Exactly, ugh.

27:43.357 --> 27:44.967
I think there's a difference

27:45.054 --> 27:47.448
between being mildly complicit
and being responsible

27:47.578 --> 27:50.016
for the sum evil
of the modern Republican Party.

27:50.146 --> 27:52.409
"Mildly complicit." Oh, dear.

27:54.194 --> 27:56.457
-You need another drink?

27:58.285 --> 28:00.200
No.

28:00.330 --> 28:02.593
Utter her name three times,
and she will appear.

28:02.724 --> 28:04.421
-Okay.

28:04.552 --> 28:06.597
Martha, Martha, Martha!

28:09.122 --> 28:10.950
McLendon residence.

28:11.080 --> 28:12.342
Oh, Winnie.
Thank God you answered.

28:12.473 --> 28:13.474
Martha.

28:15.694 --> 28:18.305
Um, can I call you back later?

28:18.392 --> 28:19.785
I'm-I'm in the middle
of something.

28:19.872 --> 28:21.612
No, no, no, no.
I have no time. I have no time.

28:21.700 --> 28:22.483
I ha--I don't know
what's happening here,

28:22.613 --> 28:23.876
but I'm being held prisoner.

28:24.006 --> 28:25.355
They're holding me here.
They're keeping me here.

28:25.486 --> 28:26.617
Who's keeping you where?

28:26.748 --> 28:28.271
It's got something to do

28:28.402 --> 28:29.664
with this Watergate break-in.
McCord was there.

28:29.795 --> 28:30.621
Read something
about it in the paper.

28:30.752 --> 28:32.493
I don't know what it is,
but just--

28:32.623 --> 28:34.277
Okay, Martha, can you
just slow down, all right?

28:34.408 --> 28:36.453
Start at--start the beginning.
What's happening?

28:36.540 --> 28:38.542
-I j--
-Martha?

28:38.629 --> 28:40.109
-Oh, God.
-Can you hear me?

28:40.240 --> 28:42.068
Get away from me. Winnie?

28:42.155 --> 28:43.678
-Hello!
-Get away from me.

28:43.809 --> 28:45.419
-Hand me the phone.
-I--

28:45.506 --> 28:46.855
-Get away from me!
-Martha!

28:46.986 --> 28:48.117
No! Please get away from me!

28:48.248 --> 28:50.206
-No!
-Ma--

28:53.122 --> 28:54.602
-Barry! Get her!

28:56.256 --> 28:58.867
-Mrs. Mitchell--

28:58.998 --> 29:01.000
-No! No! Let me go!
-Calm down.

29:01.130 --> 29:03.350
Get off of me! Leave me alone!

29:03.437 --> 29:05.831
-Get off me!

29:05.961 --> 29:07.049
Mrs. Mitchell,
calm down!

29:23.936 --> 29:25.546
Mrs. Mitchell.

29:25.676 --> 29:29.724
You're okay. You're okay.

29:29.855 --> 29:31.944
Give me your hand.

29:32.074 --> 29:34.424
-Let me help you.

29:34.555 --> 29:36.122
Here, here. It's okay.

29:36.252 --> 29:36.992
It's okay.
I'm not gonna hurt you.

29:37.123 --> 29:37.906
Give me your hand.

29:42.693 --> 29:45.435
-Ah! God damn it!

29:45.566 --> 29:48.438
You broke my fucking finger,
you bitch!

29:53.748 --> 29:55.315
Get my bag. It's there.

29:55.445 --> 29:57.621
Don't fucking move.

29:57.708 --> 30:00.233
Please!
Please don't hurt me anymore.

30:00.320 --> 30:03.149
Please. Please.

30:03.279 --> 30:06.892
I'm sorry. Please.

30:07.022 --> 30:08.763
I promise I'll be quiet.
Please. I'm sorry.

30:08.850 --> 30:10.765
I'm sorry. I'll be quiet.

30:12.593 --> 30:14.290
Hurry up.

30:16.727 --> 30:17.990
Please don't. Please--

30:39.620 --> 30:44.451
Oh, fuck. Oh, God. Yeah.

30:44.581 --> 30:46.714
-John.
-Almost. I'm just--oh, God.

30:46.801 --> 30:47.671
Fuck.

30:52.415 --> 30:53.547
-Uh...
-Yeah?

30:53.677 --> 30:54.940
-...necklace.
-Oh, sorry.

30:55.070 --> 30:56.463
-It's just--
-That's okay.

30:56.593 --> 30:57.943
No, wait.

30:58.073 --> 30:59.814
I can--I-I can get it back.

30:59.945 --> 31:01.424
It's--oh, shit.
Is it out? Fuck.

31:01.555 --> 31:03.078
We can just--it's-it's--

31:03.209 --> 31:04.340
Oh, my God. I'm so sorry.

31:04.471 --> 31:06.777
Oh, my God. Jesus Christ.

31:06.908 --> 31:08.257
-Ugh.
-It's okay.

31:11.086 --> 31:14.307
Every woman dreams of a man
who'll go for a full hour...

31:14.437 --> 31:15.786
and a half.

31:15.917 --> 31:16.787
I'm sorry.

31:17.658 --> 31:18.572
Oh fuck.

31:21.880 --> 31:22.837
I'm gonna go
make myself a drink.

31:22.924 --> 31:24.491
No.

31:24.621 --> 31:25.666
I need to get
some writing done.

31:25.796 --> 31:27.059
-Wait. No.
-You know what? I know.

31:27.189 --> 31:29.539
I know what's
going on here, okay?

31:29.626 --> 31:32.107
It's clearly--you-you-you
stood me up last week,

31:32.238 --> 31:33.717
and you begged me
to come to D.C., and now...

31:33.848 --> 31:36.329
The president had urgent
business. I told you that.

31:36.459 --> 31:37.939
...when I'm actually here,
your mind is somewhere else.

31:38.026 --> 31:40.246
I mean, you made me
take a cab home after dinner

31:40.376 --> 31:41.769
so you could get back
to work, John.

31:41.900 --> 31:43.162
Mo, this is not about you.

31:43.292 --> 31:44.076
That's exactly
what I'm saying.

31:44.163 --> 31:45.338
I know what it feels like

31:45.468 --> 31:46.687
when a man loses interest.

31:46.817 --> 31:48.036
What? No.

31:48.167 --> 31:50.082
This is not me
losing interest.

31:52.998 --> 31:54.956
It's absolutely fine
if you're over it.

31:55.087 --> 31:56.784
I've got other friends in town,
and I-I'm just--

31:56.915 --> 31:57.698
-Wait.
-I'm gonna--

31:57.828 --> 31:59.308
I'm just gonna go out.

31:59.439 --> 32:00.614
Wait.
I don't want you to go out.

32:00.744 --> 32:02.485
How did going out
even come into it?

32:02.572 --> 32:04.574
I would just rather not
do this if it's not real,

32:04.661 --> 32:06.837
-so let's just call it.
-No.

32:06.968 --> 32:08.578
This was fun, this was a fling,
and now it's over.

32:08.709 --> 32:10.363
That's--there's nothing wrong
with that.

32:10.493 --> 32:12.147
I love spending time with you.

32:12.234 --> 32:13.409
You know how many people
I love spending time with?

32:13.540 --> 32:15.411
No people. Zero.

32:15.542 --> 32:17.805
I--look. I know you--yeah.

32:17.936 --> 32:19.589
You're right. I am distracted.

32:19.676 --> 32:21.461
I--there's a lot going on,
and, uh, you know

32:21.591 --> 32:24.377
the-the fucking Porsche shit,
and Dickie Moore

32:24.464 --> 32:26.248
-got in my head today, and--
-What?

32:26.379 --> 32:27.858
Why are you listening
to Dickie Moore?

32:27.989 --> 32:30.470
-He's angling for your job.

32:30.600 --> 32:33.690
You are here now with me.
Can you be here with me?

32:33.821 --> 32:35.475
-Yes.
-I mean, John, please?

32:35.605 --> 32:36.519
I'm sorry. Yes.

32:36.650 --> 32:37.607
-Come on.
-Of course.

32:47.139 --> 32:48.053
Wait, y-you don't think
he's actually

32:48.183 --> 32:49.010
angling for my job, do you?

32:49.141 --> 32:50.403
-Goodbye.
-Wait. What?

32:50.533 --> 32:52.318
You know what?
Why don't you just go

32:52.448 --> 32:54.233
and take care
of whatever this is

32:54.320 --> 32:56.322
that's going on
that you need to take care of?

32:57.366 --> 32:58.933
And hey, don't bother me
until you're ready

32:59.064 --> 33:00.239
to look me in the eye
when you fuck me.

33:00.369 --> 33:01.370
Hey. What?

33:04.373 --> 33:06.941
I made eye contact!

33:08.856 --> 33:10.379
Fuck you.

33:20.911 --> 33:21.782
All right, we got it from here.

33:21.869 --> 33:22.435
-Yup.
-Thank you.

33:48.591 --> 33:49.940
-Hey, Ang?
-Hmm?

33:52.334 --> 33:53.248
Perfect vantage point.

34:09.047 --> 34:12.224
Lakeview Country Club, $6.36.

34:14.704 --> 34:15.836
E. Howard Hunt.

34:18.012 --> 34:19.666
HH.

34:20.710 --> 34:23.409
Uh, let's see.
I got bad eyes here.

34:24.671 --> 34:26.542
Yeah.

34:26.673 --> 34:28.936
Yeah, that certainly does
look like my signature.

34:29.067 --> 34:31.591
So you would say
it's within possibility

34:31.721 --> 34:33.767
that that check belongs
to you, right, Mr. Hunt?

34:35.769 --> 34:37.075
Uh, sorry.
Don't get the relevance.

34:37.205 --> 34:38.902
Well, we sat down

34:38.989 --> 34:40.295
with one of the burglars
this morning,

34:40.426 --> 34:42.515
a Mr. James McCord.

34:42.645 --> 34:43.385
Don't know him.
Never heard of him.

34:43.516 --> 34:44.169
-Never?
-Nope.

34:44.299 --> 34:45.866
Mm.

34:45.996 --> 34:47.607
He was surprisingly candid
about his...

34:47.694 --> 34:49.304
leadership role
in the break-in.

34:49.391 --> 34:51.001
Oh, yeah? Well, that's great.

34:51.132 --> 34:52.873
Then you would get some
information, no doubt, right?

34:53.003 --> 34:55.223
A guy like that with his,

34:55.354 --> 34:57.791
shall we say,
retrograde racial outlook?

34:57.921 --> 34:58.792
There's no way he would have
ever thought

34:58.922 --> 35:00.098
to hire those Cubans.

35:02.012 --> 35:04.319
You got the B team
in with you today.

35:04.450 --> 35:07.279
You know what?

35:07.366 --> 35:09.107
I actually thought
the same thing,

35:09.237 --> 35:11.805
but then I figured,
hey, Italians need work too.

35:11.935 --> 35:14.242
-Terrific.

35:14.373 --> 35:17.289
Anyway, we inferred
that there were

35:17.419 --> 35:19.291
more people involved
in the break-in.

35:19.421 --> 35:22.511
Operational specialists
above McCord's pay grade.

35:22.642 --> 35:24.557
-Pardon me?
-We're talking about lookouts.

35:24.644 --> 35:25.819
Which led us
to the Howard Johnson's

35:25.949 --> 35:27.429
across the street.

35:27.560 --> 35:29.344
Perfect sight line
down to the Watergate.

35:29.431 --> 35:30.998
Front desk clerk
showed us to a room

35:31.129 --> 35:33.131
belonging to a bunch of guys
who checked out in a hurry.

35:33.261 --> 35:34.741
Guess what we found
in the trash can.

35:34.828 --> 35:36.308
Trash.

35:36.438 --> 35:38.527
Found this check
made out by you.

35:38.658 --> 35:40.225
I can't explain that.

35:41.182 --> 35:43.097
It would suggest that
you were across the street

35:43.228 --> 35:44.272
from the Watergate at the time
of the break-in, would it not?

35:44.403 --> 35:46.013
Why would it suggest that?

35:46.144 --> 35:47.754
You can make all the
suggestions you want, but--

35:47.884 --> 35:48.798
-It doesn't?
-No.

35:48.929 --> 35:50.235
-No?
-This?

35:50.322 --> 35:52.367
This is circumstantial.
This means nothing.

35:52.454 --> 35:54.021
So that check
just walked itself in?

35:54.152 --> 35:55.849
-What the fuck?
You could have planted it.

35:55.979 --> 35:57.285
Who-who knows? I don't know.

35:57.416 --> 35:58.417
Are these your kids?

35:58.547 --> 36:00.767
Those are my children, yes.

36:00.897 --> 36:01.942
-All of them?
-All of them.

36:02.072 --> 36:03.552
I--we made them all.

36:03.639 --> 36:06.207
-Both of us. Together.

36:06.338 --> 36:08.166
So what'd you-what'd you
have to eat that night?

36:08.253 --> 36:09.602
-Spaghetti.
-What kind of sauce?

36:09.732 --> 36:11.038
Oh, I know
what he's talking about.

36:11.125 --> 36:12.953
What?

36:13.040 --> 36:14.215
He wants me to admit
to my secret ingredient.

36:14.346 --> 36:16.086
Smoked "pah-pri-kah."

36:16.217 --> 36:18.001
-Oh, for fuck's sake.
-Excuse me?

36:18.088 --> 36:19.351
Hey, hey, hey, hey
With the language.

36:19.438 --> 36:20.874
Mr. Hunt, you were there.

36:21.004 --> 36:22.484
You left your check
at the scene.

36:22.615 --> 36:24.051
Guys, this is
completely circumstantial.

36:24.182 --> 36:25.922
You-you see--
you see these trash cans?

36:26.053 --> 36:28.186
Are you really gonna tell me
that the smoldering trash cans

36:28.316 --> 36:30.492
you got out there, that's not
a textbook evidence fire?

36:30.623 --> 36:32.233
The kids wanted s'mores.

36:32.364 --> 36:33.800
The kids are making
s'mores, for God's sake.

36:33.930 --> 36:36.150
-They're making s'mores.
-In a trash can fire?

36:36.281 --> 36:37.543
Do you have any other
questions for us?

36:37.673 --> 36:38.892
I do have a question.

36:39.022 --> 36:40.241
Can you point me towards,
uh, the restroom, please?

